      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/51/12",
      "text": [
        " : كَتَبْتُ إِلَى أَبِي اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ كَانَ عَلَيَّ عِتْقُ رَقَبَةٍ فَهَرَبَ لِي مَمْلُوكٌ لَسْتُ أَعْلَمُ أَيْنَ هُوَ أَ يُجْزِينِي عِتْقُهُ فَكَتَبَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ \"نَعَمْ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3526 - It is narrated from Ahmad bin Hilal, who said:\n\"I wrote to Abu al-Hasan (as), stating that I was obligated to free a slave, but my slave had escaped, and I did not know where he was. Would his emancipation suffice for fulfilling my obligation?\"\nImam (as) wrote back: 'Yes.' \""
        ]
      }
    },
